Sprint 11 changes to vendored content
-------------------------------------

Per ADR-033 (in-house gating strip policy) and ADR-034 (output-path
convention), Sprint 11 applies two surgical transformations to vendored
SKILL.md / agent files:

  1. Strip firm-branch markdown sections; keep in-house path.
  2. Rewrite invocation references: per-plugin practice profile →
     unified `~/.config/oscar/profile.json`; output paths → ADR-034's
     `~/Documents/Oscar/<Practice Area>/<Output Type>/` convention.

Per-plugin MANIFEST.md files in each directory enumerate the verdicts
(keep / drop / keep-borderline / rewrite) the orchestrator applied
during repackage.

Plugins not vendored from upstream
----------------------------------

Out of scope for Oscar GC's in-house-counsel audience or for Sprint 11
specifically:

  - law-student/        — educational; not in-house counsel.
  - legal-clinic/       — law school clinic; not in-house counsel.
  - legal-builder-hub/  — community-skills installer; Oscar GC is
                          self-contained, no community-extension model
                          (deferred to Sprint 15+).
  - external_plugins/cocounsel-legal/ — depends on a paid Westlaw /
                          CoCounsel subscription; cannot bundle in a
                          self-contained install.
  - managed-agent-cookbooks/ — scheduled-agent templates; deferred to
                          Sprint 12+ alongside the Forge meta-agent.

